Ada Wodu, Calabar The Governor of Cross River State, Ben Ayade, has approved the appointment of 427 additional aides. The Special Adviser, Media and Publicity to the Governor, Christian Ita, announced this in a press statement in Calabar, on Monday. Those appointed include chairmen and members of boards of agencies as well as special assistants. Ita added, “Some of the appointments are subject to confirmation by the state House of Assembly.” Copyright PUNCH.
